The paper discusses the use of automatic optimization techniques in industrial applications, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on improving the resilience of planners to unforeseen events, which is a common concern in software and systems engineering (cs.SE). The implementation of a diversity-aware genetic algorithm involves optimization and search techniques (cs.RO), and the analysis of parameter settings and incorporation into larger frameworks suggests a focus on machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY).
